00:02:02.270 --> 00:02:04.940
Today, we're in for a treat.

00:02:04.940 --> 00:02:07.940
Let me just share a little
bit, this is a spoiler.

00:02:07.940 --> 00:02:11.180
When the earth was formed
about 4.5 billion years ago

00:02:11.180 --> 00:02:14.150
as part of the solar
system, it was actually

00:02:14.150 --> 00:02:21.209
bombarded by a variety of
comets and Mars-sized objects.

00:02:21.209 --> 00:02:23.750
And you can see the evidence of
that, of course, in the moon.

00:02:23.750 --> 00:02:25.880
If you look at the moon, you'll
see that it's full of craters.

00:02:25.880 --> 00:02:27.260
And the only reason
the earth isn't full

00:02:27.260 --> 00:02:29.593
of craters, because it's about
the same age as the moon,

00:02:29.593 --> 00:02:32.420
is because it has plate
tectonics and it has erosion

00:02:32.420 --> 00:02:34.790
and all of that
old crust is gone.

00:02:34.790 --> 00:02:37.160
But the bottom line is
that the earth, when

00:02:37.160 --> 00:02:40.040
it was first formed,
was bombarded

00:02:40.040 --> 00:02:46.280
by such large impactors that it
partially melted at least once.

00:02:46.280 --> 00:02:52.130
And all of the carbon that
was originally on the earth

00:02:52.130 --> 00:02:54.334
must have gone
away, because it's

00:02:54.334 --> 00:02:56.500
an element that would have
just basically evaporated

00:02:56.500 --> 00:02:58.190
off the earth.

00:02:58.190 --> 00:03:00.890
One of the ideas, and
that's one of the things

00:03:00.890 --> 00:03:02.810
that our speaker today
is going to talk about,

00:03:02.810 --> 00:03:06.890
is that carbon from which we
are all made out of perhaps

00:03:06.890 --> 00:03:09.680
was implanted in the
earth by later meteorites

00:03:09.680 --> 00:03:11.370
or other objects.

00:03:11.370 --> 00:03:13.370
The importance about that
is that you should all

00:03:13.370 --> 00:03:15.550
remember that, in fact,
we're all Martians.

